cs.CV, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.HC, cs.SY 

This paper is about creating FPGA accelerators for vision algorithms using event-based cameras. The most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper focuses on implementing a stereo matching algorithm to generate a disparity map. Other likely sub-categories include cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.AR (Augmented Reality), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). These sub-categories are relevant as the paper discusses hardware acceleration and implementation of the algorithm on FPGA, which involves embedded systems and control, and can have applications in augmented reality and human-computer interaction.
